postcontent:
Ghost, Inc., G42/43 Edge Trigger Connector and Ghost reduced weight firing pin safety plunger spring. Both items are brand new in their original packaging and covered by the full manufacturer's warranty and guarantees.

The Ghost Edge Connector requires no gunsmithing and is a simple, drop-in replacement of the Glock factory connector. With this connector, you'll experience a smoother, lighter trigger pull with complete elimination of the famous "hump" in the original Glock trigger. This trigger connector is designed specifically for self-defense, and therefore the pre-travel is only slightly reduced while over-travel is nearly eliminated. You'll experience a clean, sharp break unlike the mushier experience the factory trigger provides. The lighter weight safety plunger spring will slightly reduce overall trigger weight and it does not at all impact the viability of the plunger. I run the Ghost Edge PRO connector and the same spring on both my G42 & G43, and this enhancement is a game-changer. 

Asking $25.00 cash or $26.00 if you want me to run a payment card through my PayPal card reader (their processing fee, not mine). Normally this setup would be $35 incl. shipping. I'm in the Lee's Summit area, but would be willing to meet at an agreeable location elsewhere in the KC metro area so long as it's commensurate with the item's value. postcontent:
Fazakerley British Enfield  - the finish is original, a type of baked on paint system that was invented by the British - other times known as Suncorite. According to website, the No4 Mk II (or Mk2) was adopted in 1949, with production at ROF-Fazakerley in July, 1949 until 1955. Fazakerley was the only plant to manufacture the No4 Mk2. fairly rare specimen and one to be proud of. The biggest difference in the MK2 and the MK1 is that the trigger of the MK2 is pinned to the receiver instead of the trigger guard. 
 Good smooth metal no rust or pitting. beautiful wood no cracks and action and barrel are perfectly bedded in stock., original butt plate. Good strong bore. Nice specimen! $380

postcontent:
Up for sale a Kriss Vector SDP pistol in 45 ACP. The pistol is equipped with a 5.5" barrel just as its full auto variant.  This pistol shoots very smooth and because of the recoil reduction system built into the gun. The bolt actually travels down instead of back into shoulder with normal firearms.  The pistol also has a threaded barrel with thread protector and shoots great suppressed due to 45 ACP already being subsonic.

  The pistol has been upgraded with a Kriss Arms M4 stock adapter, KAK pistol buffer extension, Sig Brace, and Odin Works locking collar.  The Vector is also equipped with a Primary Arms reflex red dot as well as Kriss factory iron sights.  The red dot really makes the pistol that much easier to shoot accurately.  The pistol also is equipped with a Magpul AFG (angled fore-grip) which is legal unlike a vertical grip due to ATF regulations.  The AFG has been modified to keep the shooters hand bend the muzzle for safety.
The KAK pistol buffer tube is Sig Brace specific and allows the arm brace to fit very tightly in combination with the Odin Works locking collar which allows you to set the position of the Sig brace on the tube.  
The pistol will also come with five 30 round factory Kriss magazines, which are not cheap!

I am asking $1700 OBO which is a good deal considering the other Kriss Vectors available either new or used on Armslist.  I am willing to sell face to face or ship to your FFL (shipping can be negotiated). You can reach me at the reply email or text message at 724seven146020.  Thanks for viewing.
